<DocsLayout title="buoy baseline" description="Manage drift baseline for existing projects">
  <h1>buoy baseline</h1>

  <p>
    Manage drift baseline to hide existing issues and only track new drift.
    Perfect for adopting Buoy in projects with existing design debt.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy baseline &lt;command&gt; [options]</code></pre>

  <h2>Commands</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Command</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>create</code></td>
        <td>Create baseline from current drift signals (hides existing issues)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>show</code></td>
        <td>Show current baseline status</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>update</code></td>
        <td>Update baseline to include current drift signals</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>clear</code></td>
        <td>Remove baseline (show all drift signals again)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Examples</h2>

  <h3>Create a baseline</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy baseline create

Found 47 existing drift signals
Creating baseline...

Baseline created: .buoy/baseline.json
Future scans will only show new drift.</code></pre>

  <h3>Show baseline status</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy baseline show

Baseline: .buoy/baseline.json
Created: 2024-01-15
Signals: 47 baselined
New since baseline: 3</code></pre>

  <h3>Update baseline</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy baseline update

Adding 3 new signals to baseline...
Baseline updated: 50 total signals</code></pre>

  <h3>Clear baseline</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy baseline clear

Baseline removed. All drift signals will be shown.</code></pre>

  <h2>Workflow</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Run <code>buoy drift check</code> to see all issues</li>
    <li>Run <code>buoy baseline create</code> to accept existing debt</li>
    <li>New drift will be caught, old drift is hidden</li>
    <li>Fix issues over time, update baseline as needed</li>
  </ol>

